window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>Captain Galvin Quintos is grappling with two gut-wrenching losses in his life—first, Hardy, the enigmatic ChronoBot, and more recently, Doc Viv. Now, he's exchanged his Captain's Mount for a life of solitude deep in the Colorado wilderness.<br> <br> Intel from the Alliance raises the alarm: Earth is teetering on the brink of an impending attack. Quintos, reluctantly pulled back into service by the EUNF, finds himself up against untenable odds. The one bright spot is USS Franklin, awaiting his command, an Omninought-Class behemoth armed with the latest cutting-edge technology.<br> <br> When the assault arrives on Earth, it's a living nightmare. The Varapin have wielded an unholy power—a technology capable of transposing entire worlds. Now, stranded in a hostile star system light-years away, Earth is quickly freezing over, turning to ice. Racing against the clock, Quintos might need to strike a deal with the devil to retrieve an elusive alien technology that can reverse this cataclysm.<br> <br> Hold onto your kibbles 'n bits—this space thriller defies the ordinary. With heart-stopping space duels, unrelenting extraterrestrial adversaries, mind-bending technology, and not just one, not even two, but three captivating women vying for his attention, Quintos embarks on the journey of a lifetime.</p>"; 
